page.title: 09Canal & Bird Sanctuary
page.content:
{The Grand Union Canal The stretch of canal that we were looking at was by the railway at the middle of Old Fishery Lane.We found these facts:The canal bridge was built in 1896.Speed limit:5 mph.Depth of lock:3m,62cm.Depth of canal:2m,30cm. The stretch we were looking at was between London and Berkhamsted.
{Bird sanctuary This sanctuary belongs to Boxmoor Trust as most of the land in this area. A man locally known as Charlie looks after birds and has been known to save animals' lives.The animals and birds at the sanctuary are:5 ducks,1 duckling, 6 hens,7 geese,2 cockrels and 3 dogs. YM03200174
